<teaserText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>Insalata caprese (literally, the salad from Capri) is the perfect summertime dish for cooks in a hurry</p><p/></div></teaserText>
<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p class="p--heading-2">Introduction</p><p>Insalata caprese (literally, the salad from Capri) is the perfect summertime dish for cooks in a hurry; slicing is the hardest part. It is made of mozzarella cheese, tomatos, fresh basil and olive oil - sprinkled with freshly ground black pepper. It's also <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../Magazine%20Spring/Story%201%20-%20A%20Perfect%20Picnic/A%20Per94b228e4.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Editorial/Content/Magazine%20Spring/Story%201%20-%20A%20Perfect%20Picnic/A%20Perfect%20Picnic%20Article">easy to prepare at a picnic!</a> Cut the soft cheese and tomato with our <a xlink:show="replace" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="coremedia:///cap/resources/../../../../Products/Fall%20Campaign/Japanese%20Knife%20Product%20Teaser.xml" cmexport:path="/Sites/PerfectChef/United%20States/English/Editorial/Products/Fall%20Campaign/Japanese%20Knife%20Product%20Teaser">super sharp Japanese knives.</a></p><p class="p--heading-2">Ingredients</p><ul><li>100g Mozarella di Bufala</li><li>2 beefsteak tomatos</li><li>fresh Basil</li><li>40g arugula</li><li>sea salt</li><li>coarsely ground pepper</li><li>4 tblsp native olive oil</li><li>1 tblsp caper berries</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><ul><li>Arrange tomato and mozzarella slices and basil leaves on a large platter, alternating and overlapping them</li><li>Sprinkle salad with oregano and arugula and drizzle with oil</li><li>Season salad with salt and pepper</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Serving Suggestion</p><p>The dressing is always a drizzle of extra-virgin olive oil â€” only. Vinegar would destroy the delicate flavor of the cheese and is never used. Because this salad is so simple, top-rate ingredients are imperative: Hothouse tomatoes and rubbery processed mozzarella are unacceptable.</p><p/></div></detailText>
